cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel approach for multi-label classification in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a sequence generation model, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning models, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the selection of informative words, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses text data, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) for tasks such as image captioning.
